# My Web Development Skills

Welcome to my portfolio page! Here, I'll showcase my skills in various web technologies.

## HTML

I have strong knowledge of HTML5, including:

- Semantic markup
- Accessibility best practices
- HTML forms

Here's a simple example of an HTML structure:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My Portfolio</title>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Welcome to My Portfolio</h1>
    </header>
    <main>
        <section>
            <h2>About Me</h2>
            <p>I'm a passionate web developer...</p>
        </section>
    </main>
    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2024 My Name</p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>

## CSS

My CSS skills include:

- Responsive design
- Flexbox and Grid layouts
- CSS animations

Here's a sample of my CSS work:


css .card { background-color: #f0f0f0; border-radius: 8px; padding: 20px; box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); transition: transform 0.3s ease; }

.card:hover { transform: translateY(-5px); }

## JavaScript

I'm proficient in modern JavaScript, including:

- ES6+ features
- Asynchronous programming
- DOM manipulation

Check out this JavaScript snippet:


javascript const fetchData = async (url) => { try { const response = await fetch(url); const data = await response.json(); return data; } catch (error) { console.error('Error fetching data:', error); } };

## SQL

While I can't run SQL directly on this static site, I have experience with:

- Database design
- Complex queries
- Data manipulation

Here's an example of a SQL query I might use:


sql SELECT users.name, COUNT(orders.id) as order_count FROM users LEFT JOIN orders ON users.id = orders.user_id GROUP BY users.id HAVING order_count > 5 ORDER BY order_count DESC;

